
Nicolas turned to his friend. "Thanks."
* * * * *

It was a while later, once they got back to the apartment that Haruka let herself loose and cried her heart out. Alone in her room, she sob, with happiness and with sadness. She couldn't believe it. Just couldn't believe that finally, after years of endless searching, she had found her Sakura. She was the girl on the cat walk, wearing Mr. Tachibana gown and her priceless necklace. A necklace she herself had painstakingly designed for her own daughter. Once would say that it was fate, and Haruka truly believed in that. Fate had brought her here. Fate had finally allowed her to meet her beloved Sakura.
More tears welled up in her eyes. "I've finally found you."
* * * * *